reopened.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/generic.png","name":"Closed","id":"6","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/3","id":3,"key":"done","colorName":"green","name":"Done"}},"components":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10002","id":"10002","name":"Cloud Controller"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"customfield_13000":null,"description":"The fix for EUCA-8371 (4.3) changes the multicast address we use with JGroups. The change is via:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n/etc/eucalyptus/cloud.d/scripts/setup_membership.groovy\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nwhich I think is not defined as a configuration file (RPM) meaning it will be overwritten on upgrade.\r\n\r\nWe should either provide support for configuring an alternative multicast address (and perhaps configure it to a backwards compatible value on upgrade) or should clearly document this networking requirements change.\r\n\r\nIf upgraded systems use a value other than the default this will impact the install process for any (Java) components that are later added to the cloud.","customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=sjones","name":"sjones","key":"sjones","accountId":"557058:f5dce1b0-db45-4dd6-a0e8-3cea5effb5ce","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/037fddf6d3bf6d691a448e01136f233a?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dsjones%26avatarId%3D18300%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/037fddf6d3bf6d691a448e01136f233a?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dsjones%26avatarId%3D18300%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/037fddf6d3bf6d691a448e01136f233a?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dsjones%26avatarId%3D18300%26noRedire